<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <head>No. 601.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Cushing</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-05-06"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6,
                                1875</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>You will express to Spanish government President’s appreciation of the
                            anticipated payments, and his satisfaction at the adjustment of this
                            question.</p>
                        <closer><signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>